com.oracle.truffle.api.instrumentation

Class SourceSectionFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.oracle.truffle.api.instrumentation.SourceSectionFilter

  • public final class SourceSectionFilter
extends Object
    A source section filter represents an expression for a subset of tagged source sections that are used in an Truffle interpreter.

    Start building event filters by calling SourceSectionFilter.newBuilder() and complete them by calling SourceSectionFilter.Builder.build().

    Since:
    0.12
    See Also:
    SourceSectionFilter.newBuilder(), Instrumenter.attachExecutionEventFactory(SourceSectionFilter, ExecutionEventNodeFactory), Instrumenter.attachExecutionEventListener(SourceSectionFilter, ExecutionEventListener)

    • Method Detail

      • newBuilder

        public static SourceSectionFilter.Builder newBuilder()
        Creates a new SourceSectionFilter expression using a builder pattern. Individual builder statements are interpreted as conjunctions (AND) while multiple parameters for individual filter expressions are treated as disjunctions (OR). To create the final filter finalize the expression using SourceSectionFilter.Builder.build().
        Returns:
        a new builder to create new SourceSectionFilter instances
        Since:
        0.12
        See Also:
        SourceSectionFilter.Builder.sourceIs(Source...), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.mimeTypeIs(String...), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.tagIs(Class...), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.tagIsNot(Class...), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.sourceSectionEquals(SourceSection...), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.indexIn(int, int), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.lineIn(int, int), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.lineIs(int), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.rootNameIs(Predicate), SourceSectionFilter.Builder.build()

      • includes

        public boolean includes(Node node)
        Checks if the filter includes the given node, i.e. do the properties of the node's source section meet the conditions set by the filter.
        Parameters:
